      • writeMultipleBlock

        public byte writeMultipleBlock(byte blockAddress,
                               byte numberOfBlocks,
                               byte[] buffer)
                        throws STException
        Writes the specified number of blocks + 1 of the buffer at the specified EEPROM block address The buffer size must be a multiple of a block size (4 bytes on ST25DV) with a max size of 4 blocks.
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Block address in target's EEPROM where to write the data contained in buffer
        numberOfBlocks - Must be less than MAX_WRITE_MULTIPLE_BLOCKS. The tag will write (numberOfBlocks + 1) blocks in its EEPROM.
        buffer - Data to write in the limit of 4 blocks (16 bytes on ST25DV)
        Returns:
        Throws:
        STException

      • writeMultipleBlock

        public byte writeMultipleBlock(byte blockAddress,
                               byte numberOfBlocks,
                               byte[] buffer,
                               byte flag)
                        throws STException
        Writes the specified number of blocks + 1 of the buffer at the specified EEPROM block address. The buffer size must be a multiple of a block size (4 bytes on ST25DV) with a max size of 4 blocks.
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Block address in target's EEPROM where to write the data contained in buffer
        numberOfBlocks - Must be less than MAX_WRITE_MULTIPLE_BLOCKS. The tag will write (numberOfBlocks + 1) blocks in its EEPROM. Set to 0 to write a single block.
        buffer - Data to write in multiples of blocks (max 4 blocks = 16 bytes on ST25DV)
        flag -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        STException

        numberOfBlocks - Must be less than MAX_WRITE_MULTIPLE_BLOCKS. The tag will write (numberOfBlocks + 1) blocks in its EEPROM. Set to 0 to write a single block LSByte first
        buffer - Data to write in increments of 4 bytes within the limit of 4 blocks (16 bytes max on ST25DV)
        Returns:
        Throws:
        STException
